Former Nominated Senator Joy Gwendo will on Monday appear in court to face charges of abuse of office and theft of Sh2.2 million. She was arrested on Friday and recorded a statement with the Ethics and Anti-Corruption Commission (EACC). She was released on a cash bail of Sh100,000. The Director of Public Prosecution (DPP) had given a consent that she be charged for stealing, issuing a bad cheque and abuse of office in respect of the Sh2.2 million belonging to a cooperative society in Kisumu. The offences were allegedly committed in October and December 2016. Ms Gwendo was nominated by TNA in 2013.  